item.title: [playground] Tensorflow.Js & Typescript [1]: Quick Start
item.description: TensorFlow is one of the most well-known libraries for machine learning. The most significant advantage of TensorFlow versus other libraries is designed to simplify the development of cross-platform projects. These days, TensorFlow.js (Javascript) is a sub-project of Tensorflow that support three environments: Node.js, Web browser, and Mobile (via React Native). Unfortunately, Javascript is not a good programming language for data science projects because it is easy to make mistakes with little experience.
